==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monophthong
<hw>Mon"oph*thong</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ with
one sound; <grk>mo`nos</grk> alone + <?/ sound, voice.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A single uncompounded vowel sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A combination of two written vowels pronounced as
one; a digraph.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monophthongal</ent>⟦br⟧
